## When wiring user-account into an app

### Step 1 — Add module packs

**Backend:**

```typescript
import {ModulePackBE_Accounts} from '@nu-art/user-account-backend';

// In Storm builder chain:
.addModulePack(ModulePackBE_Accounts)
```

**Frontend:**

```typescript
import {ModulePackFE_Accounts} from '@nu-art/user-account-frontend';

// In Thunder builder chain:
.addModules(...ModulePackFE_Accounts)
```

### Step 2 — Configure session JWT signing

The default JWT secret key is `'jwt-signer--account-session'` (resolved via `ModuleBE_SecretManager`). Override in config if needed:

```typescript
ModuleBE_SessionDB: {
  sessionTTLms: 86400000,   // 1 day (default)
  rotationFactor: 0.5,       // refresh at 50% TTL remaining (default)
  maxPrevSession: 10,         // max linked sessions to keep (default)
  jwtSigner: {
    secretKey: 'my-custom-jwt-key',
    projectId: 'my-project-id', // optional
  }
}
```

