## When creating sessions from an auth method

Auth method modules (password, SAML, passkey) create sessions after verifying credentials:

```typescript
import {ModuleBE_SessionDB} from '@nu-art/user-account-backend';
import {MemKey_AccountId} from '@nu-art/user-account-backend';

// Set the account context:
MemKey_AccountId.set(account._id);

// Create session and set JWT on response:
const initialClaims = {
  accountId: account._id,
  deviceId: body.deviceId,
  label: 'my-auth-method',
};
await ModuleBE_SessionDB._session.create.andReturn({initialClaims});
```

- Use `_session.create.andReturn` when the response should carry the JWT (most login flows).
- Use `_session.create` when you need the `DB_Session` object (e.g., to embed the JWT in a redirect URL — SAML pattern).

