## When adding custom session claims

Implement `CollectSessionData` in your module:

```typescript
import {CollectSessionData, BaseSessionClaims} from '@nu-art/user-account-backend';
import {TypedKeyValue} from '@nu-art/ts-common';

type MySessionKey = TypedKeyValue<'myKey', { someValue: string }>;

export class MyModule_Class
  extends Module
  implements CollectSessionData<MySessionKey> {

  async __collectSessionData(data: BaseSessionClaims): Promise<MySessionKey> {
    return {
      key: 'myKey',
      value: {someValue: await this.computeSomething(data.accountId)},
    };
  }
}
```

The returned `{ key, value }` is merged into the JWT claims. The key must be unique across all modules that implement `CollectSessionData`.

---

## When resolving accounts in an auth method

Use `findOrCreateByEmail` for login flows where the account may not exist yet (SAML, OAuth):

```typescript
import {ModuleBE_AccountDB} from '@nu-art/user-account-backend';

const account = await ModuleBE_AccountDB.findOrCreateByEmail(email, 'user');
```

For flows where the account must already exist (password login, passkey login), query directly and throw if not found.

---

## When reading session data on the frontend

```typescript
import {SessionKeyFE_Account, StorageKey_DeviceId} from '@nu-art/user-account-frontend';

// Get the current account from session:
const account = SessionKeyFE_Account.get();

// Get the device ID (always available after module init):
const deviceId = StorageKey_DeviceId.get();
```

